reviews: One of the big trend (understandable) in Paris is to double (if not more) the price of a room if there is a big event in Paris or in the hotel's area. I had it for the Fashion Week, now I got it because of a huge event at Porte Maillot. I booked late so all my usual hotels were fully booked or overprized. Until I got to the Saint Ferdinant. Price was higher but remains reasonable. As expected for a 4 stars hotels in Paris, breakfast is good, with enough choices. Staff is making the difference. Very friendly and helps a lot. They also changed their policies and are proposing ecofriendly options like having a free refill point for water. And they propose a bottle in case you do not have your own with you. Rooms are clean and surprisingly, very quiet even if it is a room facing the street. Good experience to recommend.

Very good hotel with grate friendly staff good location good service and a coffee machine in lobby with free coffee. Higher than I expected üëçüëçüëçüëç I recommended this hotel. Many restaurants and bar near there and a super market is front of hotel. And 10 min walking to champs elyas.

I stayed here on Business, I could walk to work. I like this hotel, the staff are very friendly and helpful. Check in was efficient. Ordered a taxi to the airport the night before, it showed up on time. Room is spacious by Paris standards! There are some great restaurants on the circle a few steps from the front door. The Argentine metro is a 5 min walk, that is a straight shot to the Louvre if you like. The Arc is a 10 min walk.

This was a wonderful hotel for my first stay in Paris. The hotel location was very central to my business and for walking the city.

More importantly, the hotel manager Zoheir Tchouar went way above the call of duty in trying to help me deal with a taxi driver who had cheated me on the ride from CDG on a Strike Day (it was quite scary with the driver claiming a surge and taking me to 2 ATMs). Mr. Tchouar actually took me to the police station to file a report which took a big chunk of time out of his busy schedule. I was hoping to write this review after learning the police had caught the guy but, unfortunately, even all the CCTV coverage didn't help them find him.

Still, Mr. Tchouar's swift and gracious action turned a terrible situation into a not so terrible one. He truly made my first impression of Paris a much better one. Thank you!

I enjoyed my stay very much. Fabio welcomed me and gave some good advice on tours. All the staff were very nice and helpful. I liked the breakfast. Its a great location. I have good memories of the holiday.

Perfect for short break. Rooms small but well furnished with tea and coffee plus good toiletries. Well situated and very helpful staff. Easy access to metro. Breakfast room being refurbished but didn't impact our stay. Will return in the future.

Hotel is good , George at the reception is Amazing.
Great service , very kind , and helpful!
He helps with the rooms , with Paris attractions and really make your stay joyful!
Appreciate it a lot !
Thank you George !

Stayed at this hotel for 3 days and we can definitely say you NEED to go here. Service by Fabiu on the first day , he helped us really well and I think we never laughed this much when arriving somewhere. Also room was clean and had enough space. The hotel is also centrally located. Nothing negative to say!

This was my second visit to this lovely, charming hotel. The location is its best part. It isolated just 5 minutes walk from Champs-√âlys√©es and 3 min walk from metro station, Argentine on probably Paris's most famous metro line. This is a small hotel; nothing fancy. It serves only breakfast (very modest, but filling). No lunch or dinner is served as the hotel has no restaurants. But there are ample of restaurants in Paris and nearby too.

Rooms are small, but decent enough. Can accommodate two people, but not with a kid or two kids. But rooms are very well - maintained and bathrooms are well stocked up too. Quality of bed and pillows are good. Good housekeeping and kitchen staff..

The hotel's manager is Zoheir Tchouar. He is now the hotel's director. In 2013 when I had visited, he was the front desk manager. It was so good to meet him after 9 years. Zoheir knows everything about Paris. He is your best guide to Paris. Extremely humble person and feels nice to see him when you walk into the hotel; you know you are in good hands. He is in charge of this hotel.

Other staff was also nice, particularly Ms Sylwia who was extremely knowledgable and patient with my queries. Special thanks to my friend Andre and Micheal also was good.

The only bad point of this hotel is one particular staff member; i think his name was Fabio. He was a very rude man. He did my checking-in and it was very unpleasant to meet him after enduring a 6-hour train journey from Amsterdam as the train was delayed by 4 hours. I had to rush for an event, and I was really late because of the train delay. So I was a bit fumbled when I reached the hotel and tried searching for the hotel reservation in my phone. Meanwhile, he asked my name twice, but since I was a bit shaken up, i didn't hear him clearly. He shouted: "I AM ASKING YOU YOUR NAME AND YOU ARE LOOKING INTO YOUR MOBILE PHONE??"

He was extremely unhelpful and un-coperative. He did not even guide me about the proper transport / train pass I should buy. He said to me: "YOU NEED TO GO STATION TO ASK THAT QUESTION." Then, Ms Sylwia was present and she later on helped me a lot after Fabio left the hotel for the day. Thankfully, he comes to the hotel only over weekends. If such an employee were to be working in any Indian hotel, he would get sacked immediately.

Other than this rude person, this hotel was great, I would highly recommend it. The location is so convenient that you can keep coming and going to this hotel several times in the day if you wish to come back to your room for some mid-day rest or something.

TIP: Book directly at the website for the best price. Take the Rue St Ferdinand street view room. And preferably on a higher floor.

I was anxious as travelling solo for the first time to attend a conference at the Palais des congress. This hotel was a 6minute walk so ideal! Also just a 10 minute walk to the arc de triumphe.
The room was clean and well presented. The staff were all incredibly welcoming and were patient with my basic French. They all were fluent in English too.
Fabio, on reception, went above and beyond - ensuring I saw at least a couple of the key sights in this beautiful city by making great suggestions and providing me with a map and advice. I can‚Äôt thank him enough for this.
They helped arrange a taxi for me back to the airport too.
There are ample restaurants within short walking distance and a little supermarket for basic supplies too.
I will definitely book back here if I return to Paris.

Very well positioned. Especially if you land at Paris Beauvais Airport. Close to the Arc de Triomphe, quiet area. Very good location, close to many sights. The location is special on a street near Porte Maillot. Beautiful view from the room, Tastefully arranged room. A special mention about the friendliness of the staff and especially a note 10 to the receptionist Fabio at the reception is an extraordinary man, who helped us to make our holiday a pleasant one, both in the hotel and and outside it. The room I stayed in was spacious, clean.

The hotel is close to the Arc Triumph and we liked very much. One of the best receptionist which I met until now, Fabio, was very kind. He helped us with everything inside and outside the hotel, to make our vacation one of the best. The hotel is clean and the rooms are big enough.

The staff were kind, helpful et tr√®s sympa! The hotel itself is small but cozy. we were upgraded to the superior room and the bed was comfortable. Room was clean and with a lovely french decor. Extra nordic and pillows. We choose to have our breakfast at the hotel and, despite some comments on this page, it was superbe. not a huge buffet but it had delicious bread, pan au chocolat and croissants freshly baked. Eggs (scrambled and boiled),sausages, compotes, yogurt, confiture Bonne mamman, and a variety of cheeses and √©piceries.

I was with my daughter for a week and the stay was very pleasant.
All the hotel staff were very friendly, especially the people at the reception who helped us locate the places of interest and how to get to them in a comfortable way.
The hotel is very well located having two subway stations just one block from the avenue, you can even walk to the triumphal arch, which is only 10 minutes walk from the hotel.
The hotel was very clean and the breakfast was good.

I had an amazing stay at the hotel Fabio the receptionist guy was awesome this guy really love his job making jokes. He takes care about customers and he knows how to make it. Thank you for everything I had a good experience at this hotel

This hotel is old and desperately in need for a renovation. Bathtub was unusable; oxidation everywhere. Breakfast very limited and cold. Bed was ok. Small lobby with no bar. Won‚Äôt go here again - NOT worth four stars. There is no Parking space; except if you get lucky and you can use the underground private parking nearby for ‚Ç¨50 per day.

On arrival Fabio immediately made us very welcome and couldn‚Äôt do enough to help us.
This hotel is in an amazing location an easy walk from the Arch de Triumph and metro.
Rooms were clean and very comfortable.
Great choice for breakfast.
I would definitely recommend.

Also I was in Paris to run the Paris marathon, the hotel is ideally located for this as it‚Äôs just a short walk to the start and finish.

we've sent 3 nights in this hotel. And i would recommend it! great location - just 5-10 minutes wallking to Ark de Triumphe. and very friendly staff, especially Fabio )

Rooms are small, but comfy. Breakfast is also really nice.

Conviniently placed near Port Maillot for an easy comute, Hotel Etoile Saint Ferdinand offers ideal accommodation in an elegant enviorement. The room is spacious and bright, so is the bathroom. The reception is open 24/7 and you are welcomed by Mr. Fabio who is professional and kind.

We was second time in Paris and our choise for accomodation was the same hotel, this coquette hotel which has a strategic situation close to Arc de Triumph, Champs Elysee, Porte Maillot and Palais de Congraises. We want to tank esspecialy to Mr Fabio and to all the staff which included Le Monsieur Directeur for for all profesional services. The hotel coffe was good and we observed the qualitee of the food ( bio milk and fresh fruits ).

Friendly and helpfull staff, very clean and quet rooms, very central, near Arc De Triomf, and very good and fare price for the hotel.

Friendly and helpfull staff, very clean and quet rooms, very central, near Arc De Triomf, and very good and fare price.

Thank you for everything we go home safetly and we will difenetly return .Thank you to Mr Fabio and to all the staff at out hotel.The hotel coffe was unexpectedly good and the croissants delicious .Perfect location close to Arc de Triumphend Champs Elysees.

The place is very convenient, as it is so close to the navette station, metro and RER. I had a very nice welcoming from mr. Fabio, at the reception, he is really focused on the guest‚Äôs wellbeing. Just near the hotel there is an excellent italian restaurant, so another plus.
The room is very quiet, with a very large bed, so it‚Äôs a good place to rest after a long day in the beautiful Paris.

Beautiful room with view vers a quiet street. Design romantic of the room. Super professional staff (maximum grade of the receptionist Fabio - thanks a lot for your kindness );
We hope until our next visit , that the bathroom will be more confortable

My fianc√©e and I spent a weekend at Hotel Etoile Saint-Ferdinand. From the moment we arrived we were impressed with the beautiful design, the exceptional location (near Charles de Gaulle - Etoile / Porte Maillot) and the lobby facilities. The staff are fabulous and we have to mention the special attention we received from Mr. Fabio - thank you very much for that! The room was very comfortable, spacious, clean, with great amenities. We highly recommend this hotel. Thanks, we can't wait to come back soon!

Hello,
I spent a weekend in this hotel. From the very first moment, I received a fabulous attention from Fabio. The room was very comfortable and clean for the price too. I fully recommend this hotel because of his staff and facilities.

Hello we stayed with my wife at 16.07.2020 - 18.07.2020 in your hotel.
We would like to THANKS üôè for very friendly service and friendly staff specially warm THANKS to Mr.Z√∂hair.
Great location great breakfast and all staff is very carefully and help for covid 19z
Hotel are is very clean and for COVID 19 always staff clean all table&chairs for customers.
Perfect !!

Many thanks for the hospitality in these difficult times.
Many thx to Fabio for strange but funny way of welcoming us. This man is of great value to the hotel!
It has a very good location. We rented a scooter, so we managed to see the city easily.

Parking at 100m of the hotel for 25‚Ç¨/day! Safe and locked away! For me, this was very important.

Thx again!

Hello everyone,

I would like to recommend this place; for the amazing location and excellent staff.
The hotel is surrounded with coffeeshops and restaurants.
There is a person at the reception called George, he is such a sweet heart.
It is sad though to see Paris with such a low number of tourists because of corona virus.

Quality price, this hotel is fair enough for a stay in Paris...

I was in this hotel in may/june 2019 and I can say that Fabio was the best concierge and wonderful gentlemen! Every suggestion he gave us for tour of beautiful Paris was a great pleasure for us. We're very grateful for that! Hope to come back again soon!

Clean, nice-looking room. We loved the corridors leading from the elevator to the rooms, very nicely decorated, red and gold, it looks brilliant. Great approach to the customer. Greetings in particular for Mr. Fabio :)

Great little hotel in Paris, but 3 not 4 star by any reasonable international measurement. Located on a quiet safe side street minutes from the metro line 1.

Bright clean rooms tastefully decorated with good sized bathrooms (rare in the Paris), excellent Wi-Fi

Avoid the 6th floor, the noise from the machine room of the lift is likely to annoy you. Thankfully the hotel is quiet at night so you probably won't get disturbed

Visited Paris just for a weekend to catch up with friends. The hotel is conveniently placed in a quite and calm neighbourhood, strategically close to metro line 1 (Argentine stop), which was one of the few lines working during recent strikes. Hence, you can get to the city centre in 10/15 mins (Louvres, Centre Pompidou, Marais, Bastille etc...). Rooms would greatly benefit from renovation and sound insulation, however this was kinda offset by the price. Up to this point it would have been 3 stars review, however I then met Fabio who literally impressed me, shortly put he is a STAR. He clearly enjoys his work and can't wait to help and sort things out for you. Moreover, he can explain you where to go and how and share valuable tips in something like 15 (fifteen!!) languages (7 fluent and another 8 at acceptable level), always wearing a nice and warm smile under his moustaches. His kindness is well worth another star and your visit, especially if you are new in town and you want to make the most out of it.

Although it was near the Arch De Triumph, the location was good.
The rooms however were very tiny and conjusted.
Small rooms with good washroom. The staff was helpful.
The hotel rooms were very noisy as you can hear one rooms noise in the other. No privacy.

It is just a simple 3 stars hotel. The room basic. We asked for a room with 2 beds and they gave us with difficulty... There is no mini bar and the breakfast was very basic...
The staff very friendly. The location near the metro...
It is not a bad choice but you pay for 4 stars hotel and we will have the amenities of 3 stars hotel....
I made them the question ‚Äú how you can wash your hands in this basin???‚Äù But they did not know anything....

Paris is one of the most beautiful places I have ever seen and Fabio has one of the most beautiful spirits I have ever met. He was extremely knowledgeable of the city and offered helpful advice for navigating around productively. He's a kind soul and the person you want to greet you in the "city of love." The hotel was also amazing. It is convenient to transportation yet nestled away to enjoy the local culture and scenery.

From the time we arrived until the time we left we received simply amazing service.

Great neighbourhood with lots of restaurants, grocery stores, and shops.

The room was perfectly sized for a Paris hotel with a nice comfortable bed and pillows. The breakfast had everything you need from eggs, sausage, cheeses, meats, bread, yogurt, coffee, juice, cereal....you name it they have it.

The front desk staff, especially Fabio, was amazing during our 3 day stay. He even took the time to arrange us a cab back to the airport for the same price as the bus.

We visit Paris frequently and will be staying here again and again.

This hotel had everything needed for a wonderful stay- good accommodations, lovely views from the window, and good breakfast. But what made this place so special were the people at the front desk. They were so helpful and went above and beyond from providing detailed Metro directions to helping to sort car rental reservations (thank you, Sylvia!). The location is great, walking distance to several landmarks and the Wi-fi is fast and reliable.

We had the pleasure of staying at this hotel in a Paris! As this was our first trip to Paris, we would say that everything about the hotel met our expectations and went beyond. The staff are wonderful. Especially, Georges and Andres, both of whom were at the front desk. Anything we asked about or asked for was met with their enthusiasm and friendly manner.

I loved staying at this hotel. I'm fortunate that I met the receptionist Fabio because he greeted my sister and I with open arms. It's not often to have someone who does exceptional effort to make guests feel like their part of the family. I already missed that aspect so much after leaving the hotel. Anyway, all the basic amenities are there, and everything are well organized. I hope I get to see Fabio again because he did an excellent job on customer service. We need more people like him

We spent a wonderful weekend in this hotel. Location is more than pleasant, its about 10 minutes walking from Arc de Triomphe. Everything was perfect. Clean and nice room, delicious breakfast, especially very kind staff. I would like to send special thanks to Fabio :) , the receptionist. May all the people in this business act like him. We will definitely go back there.

Very nice hotel in an excellent location 15 minutes from the Arc de Triomphe and not far from the Porte Maillot stop of the Le Bus Direct shuttle from Paris CDG. A few minutes from the Argentine stop, ligne 1 and thence, 20 minutes to the Louvre Muse√© stop. Rooms are clean and tidy though small, suitable for city breaks. Competitive prices, great value overall. Rooms always turned over, if sign left on door. Breakfast decent and varied. Staff are very friendly and helpful, especially Fabio and Georges. Comfortable lobby with free coffee and nice couches.Compute and printer for check in. Perfect hotel for a couple wishing to see the sites of Paris on an affordable budget.

The hotel is very accessible by public transportation. However, it was much smaller than it looked like in the pictures (in term of rooms and breakfast).
- The breakfast is poor.
- no dinner
- the breakfast room is very very small

But the Staff is very kind :)

Our 4-night-stay in this hotel was really nice. The building and interior is not new, that is true, and the whole place is very small but charming and the location is very convenient. I found the hotel very clean which was the most important for me.
And let`s not forget the staff. Thank you for George - your greeting at the check in was a really great start for our stay. Another staff member (Andre, maybe?) was also very nice and helpful when asked for help. And people often mention Fabio in reviews - not surprising, he is a great asset to your place when it comes to customer service. The end of a holiday can be depressing, but thanks to him we left with big smiles.
I would definitely recommend this hotel and would come back again.

This hotel is in an good location close to the Arc de Triumphe. Hotel is very clean and staff is kind and helpful. Fabion is a good Hungarian pronunciation. I would recommend it to others, I would be happy to return to this hotel.

Spent 4 nights here end of June 2019. On a quiet street short walk to metro station. Elevator is tiny. Rooms clean. Visited during heat wave and was always offered cold water. A little thing that shows quality. Did not have breakfast but coffee machine fine. Pastry shop very near. Did not get name man working desk when I arrived. Had short wait as I was early and others checking out. Heard him use at least 3 languages in dealing with clients. Special thanks to George who helped me arrange an evening out.

Clean room with a lovely view. Georges at the front desk made the stay the best ever! Lovely bakery just around the corner for breakfast.
Although safe never worked properly, coffee and snacks waiting in reception area made for a nice welcome back in the evening.

The hotel is a lovely quaint place that does everything a city hotel needs to do. The staff are superb with a special thankyou to Fabio and Sylwia.
We were checked in by Sylwia who went over and above what we could expect from anyone in this role. She spent time and effort in explaining the hotel and the area around it, making sure that we were aware of every detail we needed for our stay.
The room was adequate if not a little tired. The air conditioning was much needed due to the 30 deg + heat.
The area the hotel was situated was really chic with a couple of really good restaurants and bars in the area.
Fabio went out of his way to make sure our stay was complete.He organised trips and airport transfers and always had a pleasant comment to make when we arrived or left the hotel
We would definitely return to the hotel if not only to get the welcome and treatment from the staff.

Good location, just a few minutes walk from Arc de Triomphe with a nearby underground station to access all parts of the city. Andre was really helpful before our visit and recommended and excellent restaurant overlooking the river and the Eiffel Tower. Fabio recommended a great river cruise company.

We had an amazing vacation in Paris, we enjoyed the hotel, the area, the staff. Everyone in the hotel was very nice and helpful, especially Fabio the Fabulous :)
We kindly recomand this hotel. Hope to come back soon.

We visited this Hotel from 3rd to 5th May. The Staff is extremly friendly, it was always a plessure talking to them. The Room was clean but a little bit small (typical for Paris). The only negative thing was the noises. In our Room (506) we could hear everything from the street and the floor. Nevertheless after a long day walking around in Paris, we slept fine. The breakfast was good.

I would definetly come Again.

A special thanks to Fabio, our absolute friendly and sympathic staff.

What a lovely small hotel, friendly and conveniently situated. Within walking distance to A lot of the tourist attractions. We were there for the Paris marathon and walked to start and finish which was perfect! Thank you!

Attending the Paris Marathon we used this hotel as our base. It ideally suited as the Champs-Elys√©es and Arc de Trimophe are only minutes away. So also is Metro Station Argentine Line 1. Staff are very friendly and courteous. The rooms were clean and ideally suited for our needs. The Cleaning Staff cane each morning and they did a great job.
We had paid for breakfast and while it was good and there was a good choice, they were a little all over the place and although self service it was difficult to get something if you looked for it. This hotel was a good choice and would recommend it but the hotel needs to get the breakfast situation sorted.

We booked after reading other reviews and weren't disappointed. The hotel is located a few 100m from Argentine metro and 5 min walk to Arc du Triomphe. Fresh coffee and a gorgeous retro drinks bar in reception where the most essential thing to do is meet Fabio. He seems to be able to get you tickets to anything! When the Atelier des Lumieres was sold out a week in advance, one call and Fabio had sorted us tickets. He helped plan our itinerary and made the trip so good.
The hotel is not too big, rooms are not huge but you're in Paris so you shouldn't be spending too much time there!
A great base for a great Paris weekend.

This is a friendly boutique hotel with exceptional reception staff, willing to help with your every need (particularly, George).It is situated in a quiet neighbourhood with many cafes and restaurants. It is close to a metro station and the Arc de Triomphe. It is also only a few minutes to Porte Maillot, and the airport bus stop. The breakfast was very good as well.

The hotel was fairly standard for a four-star hotel in Europe. Very clean, just small rooms and not the best air conditioning. Fabio, one of the front desk attendants was very helpful with aiding in planning different activities and was very knowledgable and nice throughout our stay at the hotel.

this hotel is in an ideal location close to the Arc de Triumph and metro stations hotel is very clean and staff were very helpful, breakfast is more than adequate with plenty of choice, some very nice restaurants close by, rooms are little small but we only used it to sleep, again location is great.

My wife and I enjoyed our stay in the hotel. Small, boutique hotel with comfortable bed, good shower and quiet. The hotel manager, Zoeheir, was very professional and helpful. Went out of his way to answer questions, even made reservations for us (due to lack of our knowledge of French). Close to the Arc de Triomphe de l'√âtoile and western end of the Champs-√âlys√©es. Also close to RER and Metro - either Charles deGaulle Etolle or Argentine. Arr 17 is quieter than other areas of Paris but after a full day of sightseeing it was nice to be in a quiet area. Breakfast was what we expected and very good for European standards.

A stones throw from the Arc de Triomphe and Metro station. Although not quite 4* accommodation, the rooms were clean and adequate for a long weekend stay. Staff are very friendly and attentive. As much continental breakfast as you can eat and complementary hot drinks and biscuits in reception 24/7.

Stayed for 2 nights for a weekend.
Staff - lovely and very friendly and accomodating
Location - great location, close to the Champs de elysee and a metrolink stop 1 min or so away, but not loud or super busy.
Breakfast - Simple but nice
Room - Room was a good enough size for a couple of nights, simple and tidy. Bathroom clean and looked relatively new with towels provided. Room had a small TV and safe and bed was a good size but firm.
Would stay again for a couple of nights.

Nice and clean hotel near to metro stations and arc de trimouph and champs de elyesse but the rooms is small as most hotels in Paris. the breakfast is not rated as for 4 stars hotel and it could be better with more variety

Our tour company booked the hotel for us for two nights before we embarked on a Battlefields Tour of France and Belgium. Apparently we were supposed to be at the huge hotel a couple of streets away. What a stroke of good luck for us. We arrived early after a very long fight from Australia. We received a really warm welcome, being offered comfortable chairs and complimentary coffee/tea in the foyer. The very friendly man in reception checked us in within 30 minutes. Our room wasn't huge but nicely appointed, in a classic french style. There were fully opening french windows looking out on to a narrow street just 800 metres from the Arc De Triomphe. There were many restaurants and bars nearby and even a supermarket across the road. The breakfast room was compact but beautifully decorated and the food was really good. All of the staff we encountered were really friendly and happy to help with anything we needed. If you are looking for modern, shiny and new this is not the place but if you are after a cosy, boutique hotel in Paris look no further than this one.

My stay at this hotel was quite comfortable.Highly recommended for its location 2 blocks from the metro.The right room for 1 or 2 people, no more.Good heating I liked that they try to optimize the cleaning by asking when it does need to be done.Breakfast is a very intimate buffet, although they could vary a bit more.

A personal, small French hotel. Clean room, good powerful shower, hairdryer and safe provided. Towels have seen better days but overall good value for the price. Front of house staff very friendly, cheerful and helpful. Breakfast very nice. Ideal for a business trip and didn‚Äôt break the bank! Very central location within 5 mins walk from Arc du Triomphe

We stayed for one night before flying back home. It is a very cozy, romantic hotel. Some of the rooms might need some upgrades, however I would still recommend this hotel.
The rooms are on the very small side, thus keep this in mind.We stayed in room 502 facing the street, and even though it had a nice view of the street during the day, it was quite noisy during the night. Do not book a street view room if you are a light sleeper.
I was sincerely disappointed about the iron situation. It is very typical for the hotels not to offer irons in the rooms in fear of any fires, therefore you have to request it from the reception and return it afterwards. This is not an issue, however the iron we were provided was so dirty that you could not iron without ruining your piece of clothing. Needless to say that you are better off packing ironless type of cloths when travelling to Paris.

The Hotel seems a 3* and not a 4* hotel. Irregular room service. i've needed to hardly insist to have a frigo at the room nevertheless it have been promised. Good breakfast. Manager very Kind and friendly. Receptionists not at the same level. Good air conditioning at the room.

Good location but poor breakfast althoug tasty, no vegetables for breakfast or any fish products, supermarket type pancakes, no refrigerator in your room, badly stained carpet, smelly lobbies and very noisy rooms from outside construction. Windows are made of one layer glass so you can hear almost anything from the streets surrounding the hotel. Good internet connection and friendly staff. Hotel needs serious investment in upgrades to actually claim 4 stars, by any measure.

Clean and Cosy, in walking distance to bus to Airport as well as to Metro, plenty restaurants around as well as a convenient store. Helpfull personal, to be used rather on week end with competitive rates

This was not our first time in this well-located hotel. It‚Äôs small and cozy, with clean, comfortable rooms and a good breakfast. What makes this hotel exceptional for me is the warmth of the staff. We will definitely be staying here again.

Let me start by acknowledging that other travellers will have had different experiences from what we had at this hotel. I understand that others may be willing to tolerate some things in a hotel that my wife and I won't tolerate. Cleanliness is a must - lack of it is a deal-breaker for us.
We booked the Saint Ferdinand from a Travelzoo offer - it looked fine and the price was good. The pics looked ok and a google streetview I did seemed ok as well.
We arrived as scheduled but that is where the good time ended. We checked in and were given room #303. This is a small hotel - the rooms are not that big, the hallways not much wider than one person and the elevator was just big enough for us and our luggage.
Room 303 is a small room but that wasn't the problem. The problem was the badly stained carpet on both sides and the foot of the bed. Trust me when I say, I am not talking about just two or three stains - this was badly stained. In my opinion, any reasonable hotel manager would have replaced it long ago or at the very least, not rented the room with the carpet in that condition.
For us, the next question was - just what does this mean for the cleanliness of the rest of the room? We sat there contemplating our next move - do we stay and put up with this, ask for another room or get out of there all together. We just couldn't get over the stained carpet so we opted to book elsewhere. When we returned to the reception desk, George ( a nice guy) was rather shocked when we told him what the problem was. He conferred with a lady whom I believe was a manager and she offered to find us another room. We declined again mentioning the stained carpet and said we'd already booked elsewhere (which we had thanks to Hotels.com). George called us a taxi and we got out of there asap!

Two things I've wondered about since:
1) why would a hotel not replace carpet that badly stained?
2) how can they promote themselves as 3 or 4 star (don't recall which it was) when they have even one room as bad as #303 was?

I can't answer these questions but I can suggest to all travellers that they should avoid the Saint Ferdinand or if they do want to stay there, do some research first and tell them no to room 303.

Also note in an effort to be fair to the hotel, I have emailed them twice since returning home regarding our experience - NO response has been received.

So there you have it! This was our experience at this hotel and I am happy to end by saying the hotel we moved to was a true 5 star hotel and we were able to end our vacation in comfort ....and cleanliness!

A charming and sweet boutique hotel in a fantastic position for a weekend in Paris. The staff were amazing and couldn‚Äôt be of more help. They were always polite and happy. It was such a delight to spend the weekend with them and will definitely be returning. Thank you for a lovely weekend.

This is a small hotel which is located a few minutes walk from the Argentine Metro and only five-10 mins from Arc de Triomphe. There is a Carrefour supermarket across the road from the hotel which is good for getting supplies. There are also a variety of restaurants, shops and a bakery nearby but sadly in August, a large majority were closed for holidays. The staff are really helpful and can‚Äôt do enough for you especially Georges. The beds are comfy and the rooms are a good size and nicely decorated. WiFi is free and worked fine when my family used it and there is a safe in the room also. The breakfast had a good selection of juices, pastries, yogurts, fruit, cold meats and cheeses and sometimes pancakes. Scrambled and boiled eggs were available along with sausages. The lady who runs the breakfast service kindly provided decaf coffee and toast on request. She was rushed off her feet and could‚Äôve done with help as the tables were always waiting to be cleared when we came down to breakfast and she struggled to keep up with demand. Unfortunately I had to invest in earplugs after not being able to sleep for most of my first night due to the road noise outside and also noise inside the hotel itself. The double glazing is not sufficient when mopeds and delivery trucks are driving by in the night and also the plumbing in the hotel needs updating as if someone flushed a loo, the cistern could be heard filing back up for around ten minutes each time and sounded like a hairdryer on high speed. Soft close fittings to the doors and wardrobes would also stop the banging from other guests rooms. I did enjoy my stay but for light sleepers I‚Äôd suggest you seek alternative accommodation or bring earplugs! The keycards didn‚Äôt work on quite a few occasions also which meant a walk down the stairs to reception. There was no ironing board or fridge in the room which for a 4 star hotel I would‚Äôve expected. There were free drinks in the lobby (rather than the cheese and wine that had swayed us to book this hotel after reading other reviews) however no decaf available and the honesty bar wasn‚Äôt stocked very well so we bought our drinks across the road at the very reasonable Carrefour, which doesn‚Äôt shut until 11pm. With a few tweaks this could be a great hotel but if I returned to Paris I wouldn‚Äôt stay again regrettably because a good nights sleep for me is an absolute must!

The hotel was clean and comfortable. Breakfast was excellent. The hotel‚Äôs location is a short walk from many Paris attractions. The desk, restaurant and cleaning staff were excellent particularly Laura. Highly recommended.

Although the hotel building and equipment are relatively old, such weakness is largely covered by its good location (Metro line 1, which is the trunk of metro network in Paris, is available. The stations of airport shuttle bus are not so far.) . Some cafes and mini-supermarkets are available in a just short walking distance. Hotel people are nice and sympathetic. A small but nice mini-drink bar is available for free in the afternoon in front of the reception.

I had a fantastic stay there recently. Excellent location. Easy walking distance to Champs-Elyses area and to local metro stations. Cute little grocery store directly across the street. Super friendly hotel staff. Answered all questions about transportation or how to find places, always a happy greeting when people walk in. Delicious breakfasts, clean rooms. Would definitely stay there again.

Lovely 2 night stay at the Saint-Ferdinand. Great location about 8 mins from the Arc de Triomphe. Breakfast was nice, served until 10.30 which is good for the weekend. Rooms were nice, good size. Staff were friendly, there's a couple of restaurants and bars in the same road which was good. We'd happily stay ahead not overly luxury, but convenient, comfortable, pretty reasonable price.

This is a nice little hotel. The rooms are not expansive, but they are comfortable. The staff is always at the ready to help or smile. Breakfast, American Style mostly, was free and nice to have. Near the hotel are great restaurants, a genuine French Bakery, and a Hertz if you need it. I was able to walk to the Arche de Triomphe. And Finally, the price is not a stretch at all. It worked well for me.

We spent 3 nights at the Saint-Ferdinand. It‚Äôs a small 40 room hotel. The room was a bit larger than the typical Parisien room. Very clean with a VERY comfortable bed. There was a electric kettle with tea and coffe in the room. An espresso machine is available in the lobby 24 hours a day. Breakfast had a somewhat limited selection but considering the fact that it is a small hotel, it had everything needed - eggs, cheeses, ham, variety of breads etc. etc. The staff were very friendly and helpful. I love the location. There are several great restaurants outside the hotel and it is a 5 minute walk to the Metro‚Äôs 1 line.
Overall, we had a great stay. Very good value for money.

Nice, clean hotel. Near arc The triomph and paleis de congres. IDeal place to stay. Simple but good enough breakfast. Nice neighbourhoud, not to busy or noisy. Good value for your money. Next time we Will be in Paris we Will choose again for This hotel.

The hotel is very nice, clean and very nicely furnished. It has a nice Parisian charm. It is located just a few steps from the metro station and it's very close to Port Maillot. Even though it is located in a very busy area, rue Saint Ferdinand is a small street and not very trafficked, therefore the rooms are not noisy at all. Breakfast is nice and served in a small but comfortable room at the ground floor. The staff is also very kind. Recommended.

Stayed in Paris for one week and picked this hotel for a 2 night stay and later moved on to a different part of Paris. We were sorry we didn't stay here for the entire week! The hotel has very convenient location to the Metro ( one block to Argentine station).The little village of Saint Ferdinand had several cafes and bistrosand restaurants very close by.Mini grocery store across the street for any needs. Also a great Fromagerie across the street.The room was very clean with comfortable bedding. Breakfast in the morning was very nice and coffee available in lobby day and night. The staff here was great! In terms of helpfulness and their very pleasant personalities, Sylvia and Usmane deserve a special mention!

I was only in Paris a couple of days to visit friends and attend Roland Garros. The Hotel Saint Ferdinand was exactly what I needed. Very convenient location, friendly service and reasonable price (for Paris).

Overall night was a disaster
You can hear everything, from the water pipe to the hair dryer or even the lift door

Only positive point would be the position, close Porte Maillot.

As a summary I would next time take another hotel

Love this hotel. Stayed there for many years for business and family trips. Initially it was for a conference at L'Etoile, but now is our hotel of choice in Paris. Great location. This year it was for the tennis at Roland Garros,. Will be there next year.

The hotel is located 5 min walking to the arc de triomphe.The room size is good for paris, and the bed size is great,the hotel is clean but the bathroom amenities needs renovation the shower leaks water. As for the staff there was only one person, so i had to go down to the reception to get an extra towel in a four stars hotel in paris? The breakfast is really poor i don‚Äôt recommend booking it with the room just go out and have breakfast in a cafe, there are lot of them around. I am not sure how they rate the hotels stars in paris but i have stayed in a 4 stars before and this one should not be a four stars. The only thing good is the location and that is what they charge you for.

The hotel is 1 metro stop from the champs elysee, so very easy to get around. The room and en suite were immaculately clean, the staff very polite and helpful. Breakfast was plentiful including hot food but the seating is quite close to the buffet area and there's not enough space for diners to get around at busy times. Thoroughly recommended.

This was our 5th stay in Paris, a city to which I would emigrate if I could find a way to make it happen.

This hotel was great and I would 100% stay there again. We dealt with three members of staff during our two night stay and they were all super-nice and helpful. The bedroom was clean and uncomplicated, as was the bathroom. Our Juliette balcony doors opened right up and it was lovely to watch people go about their daily life in the street below.

The area was pretty nice: several caf√©s nearby who also had super-nice and helpful staff. The hotel is about 10 minutes walk from the Arc de Triomphe and the Champs-√âlys√©es.

The only problem we had was a light bulb in the bathroom which started flickering and soon drove me crazy, so I removed it. No big deal. I'm sure a staff member would have fixed promptly it if I'd asked. Also, almost all the TV channels are in French. Even the English/USA shows are overdubbed in French! That didn't bother us because we watched Netflix on my iPad using the hotel's fast, free internet.

Note to any first time visitors to Paris: *do not* get an airport taxi to your hotel. You will be overcharged beyond your worst nightmares. We were charged ‚Ç¨102! Get an Uber, or a train from the airport to Gare du Nord and get an Uber from there.

(Review also published on Hotels.com)

Sweet!

Clean and friendly. Really a good vibe. Big new bathrooms and an old school Paris feel on the inside. The walls had a particularly penetrative pale purple pattern protruding from them when I woke up at 3 am shaking from the nights adventure.

A frequent user of this hotel whilst on business, and always have a pleasant stay. It is well positioned not being far from the Arc de Triomphe and Champs-√âlys√©es. Shame the happy times wine and cheese is no longer offered though.

Stayed for 5 nights on B and B. Staff are superb. Georges on reception came to our room twice to help with safe and wifi connection. Nothing too much trouble. Large comfy bed and twin sink bathroom. Room had a fridge which was very handy for water/milk etc. Supermarket right across street.
Breakfast selection was good with boiled eggs to cook yourself. Ask if you want bread toasted and it gets done in kitchen. Several restaurants just yards from hotel. We were surprised at how expensive eating out was. On arrival our room wasnt ready so we went for a drink. A coffee, hot chocolate.and two cognacs....see photo of bill!!

The hotel is located at a very convenient location just a few by lanes from Arc De Triumph. The staff is very helpful and polite, and the rooms are neat and clean. They are not big but one or two nights is manageable, quite okay. The hotel has no restaurant of its own, so no options of lunch or dinner. Breakfast is available though.
All in all, recommended for a very good and accessible location.

Very convenient location close to metro, airport bus & Paris sights

First visit to Paris and we were not disappointed.

Lots of convenient walkable local amenities right by the hotel

Lovely comfy big bed (superior room),friendly helpful staff. Cannot fault this hotel.

We loved this hotel! The location is ideal, settled into a nice neighborhood with local bars and restaurants and a beautiful fromagerie just around the corner. Easily walkable to major tourist attractions such as the Eiffel Tour, Arc d'Triumphe and more.Very stylish, cozy and comfortable hotel.

Was in transit and stayed there for a night with my family. Location is OK.
It is near Arc De triomphe but still for tourists i would recommend to pay slightly premium and stay at better locales. They have a couple of decent cafes and restaurants right near this property (includes a carrefour store) which is a plus. Overall the rooms were small but neat and clean.
Its a small property and i would recommend it to solo business travellers. If out on a family vacation with kids you wont be super stoked about it.
Must mention the front office manager was the most helpful and friendly i have met in recent times in Europe.

Stayed in this hotel for three nights. I have traveled all over the world, this is by far one of the best hotels that I have seen five stars hospitality and service. The hotel is so clean, the room size is very adequate for Paris, location is outstanding. Special thanks for the manager of this hotel Mr. Zohair, he is extremely friendly, caring for every customer, getting out of his way to provide an outstanding service. Also the breakfast is wonderful with plenty of variety, overall outstanding experience.

We visited Paris during christmas and stayed in this hotel for 3 nights. The booking site had mentioned this as a 4-star, but it was no way near to that.
Positives:
- Polite and courteous staff
- Decent location with access to Metro

Negatives:
- Rooms are very small
- Room walls are so thin we could hear the people talking in the next room
- Street sometimes would get noisy.
- Breakfast is very minimal.

I stayed here for a weekend with a friend in a twin room. I thought the hotel was nice but I had previously stayed in r Kipling hotel and I really loved it but didn‚Äôt really love this one so I was slightly disappointed. We booked a twin room but had to ask for it on arrival as we got a double. The room was nice but a bit dated and a tile was off in the bathroom. We weren‚Äôt spending much time in the room so it wasn‚Äôt a big deal. The breakfast is fab, plenty to choose from and really tasty. The happy time at the time of booking was supposed to be wine but had since changed to juice which was disappointing as this was our main reason for choosing this hotel . However we asked at the reception and the lovely lady Laura was so nice about it and gave us our wine that we would have had. I felt uncomfortable asking but Laura totally made us feel at ease and welcome and understood that we were really looking forward to the wine, two girls in Paris for the weekend, it really helped with our budget !
Overall The beds were really comfy, the room was clean, breakfast was delicious and we had a lovely stay. I would still recommend the happy coulture hotels as they help so much with a budget but out of preference hotel r Kipling is more modern and a nicer atmosphere to stay.

Very friendly staff with confortable rooms. The breakfast was small but sufficient. Location was very close to the congress center and shopping district. Bathrooms were clean and largs with a bath and shower.

Stayed for one night on a business trip to Paris with colleagues. Excellent receptionist very welcoming. Small bar area but great for a quiet social drink. Bedroom was great, perfectly clean and quiet, mine was on the fifth floor 501. Would definitely stay again.

Location near the Arc de Trioumpe and the Metro made for easy access to food, shopping and commute to other places of attraction.
Staff was also most helpful and I love the coffee/tea and refreshments laid out at the lobby :)
